    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="1464"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1464">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/488.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Bevan</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                    <note n="132" xml:id="d1464fn132">Communicated to the Spanish Ambassador
                        December 24, 1914.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tampico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 22, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Julian Zorrilla was released this evening upon payment of 10,000 pesos and
                    condition he would leave Mexico immediately by steamer. Have sent him to Sabine,
                    Texas, on oil tanker.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bevan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
